directions.Direction: Cut up the bell peppers into cubes.

Add all ingredients for the steak sauce into a small bowl.
Whisk well.
Using a medium size pan on medium heat, coat it with avocado spray.

directions.Direction: Season chicken tenders well on both sides with garlic powder, onion powder, chili powder (optional), and paprika.
Cook in the air fryer at 385 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Try not to overcook the chicken as you will have to reheat daily.
Cook your noodles following the directions on the box. Make sure to save the pasta water for later use.
For the Sauce
In a medium size sauce pan on low/medium heat, coat with some avocado spray.
Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute or so. Don’t let the garlic burn.
Add jar of Alfredo sauce plus about 1/4 cup of pasta water. Allow it to simmer for a few minutes then add lemon zest & 1 lemon juiced.
Combine well and simmer for another minute.
Add the cooked pasta and coat it well with the sauce.
For the Broccoli
Coat broccoli with avocado spray then season it with salt, paprika, and garlic powder.
Cook in the air fryer at 385 degrees for 5-6 minutes. Check before time is up to make sure it is not burning. You may also steam or pan sear the broccoli instead.
To plate, add 3/4 cup of pasta, 1 cup of broccoli, and 4-6oz of chicken (about 2-3 chicken tenders).

In a medium size pot on medium heat, add drained carrots & peas and chopped onions.

directions.Direction: Minced the jalapeño and red bell pepper. Set aside
in a bowl add 4 eggs plus fat free milk. Whisk all together

In a medium size skillet, break up the chorizo links into small chunks and cook until golden brown corners. Once is done put it on a plate with a paper towel so that it absorbs some of the fat. Let it cool.
Add cooled chorizo to the egg mixture plus the minced veggies. I did not add any salt as the chorizo has a lot of flavor of its own. If you prefer to add salt go for it.

place egg mixture in a baking pan. I used two medium size containers big enough for the round cup to fit in it twice. You may also cook it in a baking sheet pan if you prefer for the patties to turn out thinner.
place baking pans into a preheated oven at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until fully cooked.
Once cooked remove from the oven. Set aside. Cut the English muffins in half and apply a tbsp or so of avocado mayo on one side of the muffin.

lay out the foil wrap pieces and a paper towel overtop. Cut out the egg mixture using anything round and almost the same size of the English muffin. I used a small round bowl. Assemble each sandwich and wrap them up.
I placed the wrapped sandwiches in a large ziplock bag and into the freezer they go.
